## Details

When debugging, it may be necessary to report detailed information to a developer. Within C#, this can be done using `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Builder` namespace methods. However, if the debugging code is not disabled when the application is operating in a production environment, then this sensitive information may be exposed to attackers.


Example:

```
        public void Configure(IApplicationBuilder app, IHostingEnvironment env)
        {

            app.UseDeveloperExceptionPage();
             app.UseDatabaseErrorPage();
        }
```


## Best practices for prevention
Debug methods should only be used in a development environment. As such, (Environment-based Startup class and methods)[https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/environments?view=aspnetcore-5.0#environment-based-startup-class-and-methods] should be added and allow debug features based on a user's environment.

Example:

```
        public void Configure(IApplicationBuilder app, IHostingEnvironment env)
        {
            if (env.IsDevelopment())
            {
                // The following calls are ok because they are disabled in production
                app.UseDeveloperExceptionPage();
                app.UseDatabaseErrorPage();
            }
        }
```

